"'''''The Game Chambers of Questal'''''" is an adventure game for [[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]] written by [[Robert Kern]] and published by [[West End Games]] in [[1990]].

The adventure background is to find, without [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] support, a missing Rebel agent that was last seen in the planet [[Questal/Legends|Questal]]. The events lead to the characters trying to escape from a kind of killer amusement park controlled by an [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Moff/Legends|Moff]].

This adventure was later re-published in [[Classic Adventures: Volume Five]] by West End Games in [[1998]].

==Publisher's summary==
''Rebel agent Tiree is missing. He never made it to the rendezvous point. Alliance command cannot spare the men to launch a full-scale search; Tiree is on his own. But one group of heroes owes Tiree more than they can ever repay&mdash;and they vow to find him.''

''Retracing Tiree's trail, the Rebels go to the planet Questal. Tiree was on an unsanctioned mission there, hot on the trail of a rumored weapon of fearful proportions. Then he disappeared.''

''Now something is hunting the Rebels.''

''Can they avoid Tiree's fate, rescue their friend&mdash;and save the Rebel Alliance?''

